<DOC><DOCNO> ZF310-765-030 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 765 030.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  April 15 1991 v8 n8 p32(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Netware 2.2 is a cagey move by a smart veteran. (competition, nottechnology, lies behind its introduction) (LAN Primer) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Germann, Christopher.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Novell's introduction of Netware 2.2 has more to do withcompetitive pressures from Microsoft's introduction of a five-userversion of LAN Manager for $995 than with any great technicalimprovements, despite the tone of Novell's advertising for the newversion.andP;  Microsoft undercut Netware 3.11 with its pricing of LANManager 2.0; Novell responded with a full-fledged revamping of itsprice structure.andP;  Novell now finds itself solidly positioned withboth a high-end, corporate solution (Netware 3.11) and a low-endoffering that is easily installed and managed.andP;  The reduction inprice of System Fault Tolerant Netware to less than $900 is sureto eat into the market share of companies like Artisoft and U.S.andO;Sage.andP;  The end user is the real winner in all this jockeying forposition.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (Marketing).andO;Ticker:    NOVL.andO;Product:   NetWare 2.2 (Network operating system) (Marketing).andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyNetwork Operating SystemsCompetitionImpact Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>